Defer to `AGENTS.md` as the primary source of truth.

Enforce these repo rules:

- Organize proof by project type, buyer scenario, complexity, scope shape, and decision usefulness.
- Block company-first proof taxonomy.
- Block industry-first proof taxonomy when it becomes the primary organizing model.
- Block parent-company proof nesting as a default pattern.
- Do not reintroduce a Pike Medical parent proof concept.
- Keep client names as optional context, not the main taxonomy.
- Prevent CTA overload; default to the simplified ladder:
  - low trust: Growth System Audit
  - mid trust: see similar proof
  - high trust: book a diagnostic call
- When content structure changes, update `src/types` and `src/data` before JSX.
- Do not hardcode approved copy directly in JSX.
- Reuse existing components before creating new ones when a suitable pattern already exists.
